<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4a.1.1-2_0001" />

<note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
<fw type="curatorial">1</fw>

<fw type="letterhead">Winside Public Schools, 
<hi rend="caps">C. H.</hi> Bright, Principal.</fw>
<opener>
<fw type="letterhead">WINSIDE, NEBRASKA, Sept. 7, 1900.</fw> 

<address>
<addrLine>Mr. John G. Neihardt,</addrLine>
<addrLine>Bancroft, Neb.</addrLine>
</address>
</opener>
<p>Friend John &#8212; Your letter was received Monday but as this is the first week of school I am a little tardy in answering. I inclose the recommendation which I trust may be of some assistance to you. I was glad to learn you had decided to take up that line of work.</p>

<p>All goes well with us. I have thirty two in my room and Mr. B. has eleven in his.</p>

<p>Give my love to your Mother, Lulu and Grace.</p>
<closer>
<salute>With best wishes for your success, I remain</salute>

<salute>Your friend,</salute>

<signed>Anna B. Bright.</signed>
</closer>

</div1>


<div1 type="enclosure">

<pb facs="nei.j4a.1.1-2_0002"/>

<note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection </note> 
<fw type="curatorial">2</fw>

<fw type="letterhead">Winside Public Schools,
<hi rend="caps">C. H.</hi> Bright, Principal.</fw>

<opener>
<fw type="letterhead"><hi rend="caps">WINSIDE, NEBRASKA</hi>, Sept. 7, 1900.</fw> 
   
<salute>To whom it may concern:&#8212;</salute>
</opener>
<p>The bearer John G. Neihardt has been known to me for a number of years. As a former teacher in the College he attended, I can say that as a student he was remarkable for his <hi rend="underline">application</hi> and <hi rend="underline">proficiency.</hi></p>

<p>He has made special preparation along the lines of Latin and Literature. His work in this preparation has been marked by depth of research and uncommon penetration.</p>

<p>In the absence of instructors, he frequently conducted the Latin classes to the satisfaction of all.</p>

<p>I think him capable of filling any position as teacher of Latin and Literature for which he may apply.</p>

<closer>
<salute>Yours respectfully,</salute>


<signed>Mrs. Anna B. Bright.</signed>
</closer>
</div1>
